PN\">{{cite book | last = Peszke | first = Michael Alfred | authorlink = Michael Alfred Peszke | title = Poland's Navy, 1918\u20131945 | publisher=[[Hippocrene Books]] | date = February 1999 | isbn = 978-0-7818-0672-5| page = 37}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Poland's Holocaust: Ethnic Strife, Collaboration with Occupying Forces and Genocide...\">{{cite book |author=Tadeusz Piotrowski |title=Poland's Holocaust: Ethnic Strife, Collaboration with Occupying Forces and Genocide\u2026 |year=1998 |publisher=McFarland & Company |isbn=978-0-7864-0371-4 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=A4FlatJCro4C&pg=PA295&lpg=PA295&dq=1939+Soviet+citizenship+Poland | via=Google Books |author-link=Tadeusz Piotrowski (sociologist) }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Polish War, German Losses\">{{cite news|title=Polish War, German Losses |newspaper=The Canberra Times |date=13 October 1939 |url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/2513833|accessdate=17 January 2009 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Seidner, ''Marshal Edward \u015amig\u0142y-Rydz Rydz and the defence of Poland'', p. 312</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">''Wojna Obronna Polski 1939'', p. 851</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceC\">KAMIL CYWINSKI, ''Waffen und Geheimwaffen des deutschen Heeres 1933\u20131945''</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SCHULENBURG\">[http://avalon.law.yale.edu/20th_century/ns069.asp Telegram]: The German Ambassador in the Soviet Union, (Schulenburg) to the German Foreign Office. Moscow, 10 September 1939 \u2013 9:40 p.m. and [http://avalon.law.yale.edu/20th_century/ns073.asp Telegram 2]: he German Ambassador in the Soviet Union (Schulenburg) to the German Foreign Office. Moscow, 16 September 1939. Source: The Avalon Project at Yale Law School. Last. Retrieved 14 November 2006</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SDtW\">{{cite book |title= Stalin's Drive to the West, 1938\u20131945 |last=Raack |first=Richard |year= 1995 |publisher=Stanford University Press |isbn=978-0-8047-2415-9 |page=58|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=pAdZMaWn8cIC&pg=PA58&dq|